iographers]]\n[[Category:English biographers]]\n[[Category:English historians]]\n[[Category:English translators]]\n[[Category:19th-century translators]]\n[[Category:Spanish\u2013English translators]]\n[[Category:Burials in Cumbria]]\n[[Category:English male poets]]\n[[Category:Members of the American Antiquarian Society]]\n", "name_user": "Patrick1982", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eA partial list of works:+Journal of a tour in the Netherlands", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Southey"}
{"title_page": "S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni", "text_new": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Maramure\u0219 \n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Maramure\u0219 County\n|name=S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni\n|image_map              = Sacalaseni jud Maramures.jpg\n|area_total_km2         = 28.79\n|coordinates = {{coord|47|35|N|23|34|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni''' ({{lang-hu|Szak\u00e1llasfalva}}) is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] in [[Maramure\u0219 County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of three villages: Coruia (''Karuly''), Culcea (''K\u0151v\u00e1rk\u00f6lcse'') and S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni. From 1968 to 2004, it also included four other villages. These were then split off to recreate [[Coa\u0219]] and [[Colt\u0103u]] Communes.\n\n{{Maramure\u0219 County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sacalaseni}}\n[[Category:Communes in Maramure\u0219 County]]\n\n{{Maramure\u015f-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Romanian subdivision\n|type                   = commune\n|county                 = Maramure\u0219 \n|population_total       = auto\n|map_caption            = Location in Maramure\u0219 County\n|name=S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni\n|image_map              = Sacalaseni jud Maramures.jpg\n|area_total_km2         = 28.79\n|coordinates = {{coord|47|35|N|23|34|E|region:RO|display=it}}\n}}\n'''S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni''' ({{lang-hu|Szak\u00e1llasfalva}}) is a [[Commune in Romania|commune]] in [[Maramure\u0219 County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of three villages: Coruia (''Karuly''), Culcea (''K\u0151v\u00e1rk\u00f6lcse'') and S\u0103c\u0103l\u0103\u0219eni. From 1968 to 2004, it also included four other villages. These were then split off to recreate [[Coa\u0219]] and [[Colt\u0103u]] Communes.\n\n{{Maramure\u015f County}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sacalaseni}}\n[[Category:Communes in Mara